sections.text:
Application of the following preventive measures is recommended, in viticulture regions in which the climatic conditions are favourable to the formation of OTA in vine products in order to reduce endemic risk which favours the onset of the most damaging vine diseases:

– Favour vine establishment in well aerated areas while avoiding very humid areas.
– Draw up plots of land with adequate planting disposition, and vegetation architecture (trellising system) to:
• facilitate planting operations;
• avoid direct contact of grapes bunches with the soil;
• ensure good pest and disease control;
• minimise the risk of grapes sun burn;
• promote the uniform ripening of the grape.

